"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79300","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-09-01","<p>Ofcom published a consultation on the future use of the 700 MHz band on 28 May 2014. This consultation assesses the impact any loss of access to the 700 MHz band would have on the PMSE community. Ofcom will ensure the views and spectrum requirements of the PMSE community are taken into account when making any final decisions on the use of the band. The consultation document and responses can be found on Ofcom’s website:</p><p><a href="http://stakeholders.ofcom.org.uk/consultations/700MHz/" target="_blank">http://stakeholders.ofcom.org.uk/consultations/700MHz/</a></p><p>Ofcom is working with the PMSE community of users and manufacturers to mitigate the impact of any change of use of the 700 MHz band; and discussing with the regulatory authorities in other countries their approach to this issue. A key focus of their work in this area is seeking to identify and make available alternative spectrum for the PMSE community.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","206818 ; 206821 ; 206823 ; 206943 ; 206944 ; 206947","2014-09-01T10:45:24.4868725Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79300/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79300/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79300/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-22","Performing Arts: Radio Frequencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on the continuation to the UK economy by (a) West End theatres, (b) the UK theatre industry and (c) the Programme Making and Special Events (PMSE) sector of a loss of access by the PMSE sector to the 700 MHz band of radio spectrum; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mike Weatherley","Hove","Mike Weatherley","206936"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79301","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-09-01","<p>Independent sector bodies have carried out assessments of the economic contribution of the arts to the UK economy. A report by the Society of London Theatre in 2013 showed that London Theatres grossed £0.53bn in sales generating VAT receipts of £88m.</p><p> </p><p>DCMS’s Creative Industries Economic Estimates, based on data from the Office of National Statistics available on a consistent basis since 2008, show the following contribution to the UK economy from Music &amp; Visual and Performing Arts (including theatre) in Gross Value Added (GVA) terms:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>GVA £m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008</p></td><td><p>3,740</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>3,779</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>3,434</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>4,039</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>4,574</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-09-01T11:03:13.0822354Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79301/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79301/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79301/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-22","Performing Arts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the economic contribution to the UK economy of (a) West End theatres, (b) the UK theatre industry and (c) the Programme Making and Special Events sector in each year since 2004; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mike Weatherley","Hove","Mike Weatherley","206937"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79302","HM Treasury","false","2014-09-01","<p>The Government has frequent discussions with the European Commission on a wide range of issues.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Since 2001, the UK has applied a 5% reduced rate of VAT, the lowest permissible under EU law, to the supply of sanitary products.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-09-01T16:09:15.5138963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79302/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79302/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79302/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-22","Sanitary Protection: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent representations he has made to the European Commission on the removal of VAT on sanitary products; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Bob Russell","Colchester","Sir Bob Russell","206878"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79303","HM Treasury","false","2014-09-08","<p>There are no current plans to introduce legislation to require all retail banks to offer secure automated messaging services to customers.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-09-08T15:28:12.4009989Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79303/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79303/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79303/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-22","Banks: Telecommunications","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will introduce legislative proposals to require all retail banks to offer a secure automated messaging services for customers.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","206966"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79304","HM Treasury","false","2014-09-02","<p>On the 8<sup>th</sup> July 2014, Mark Carney, the Governor of the Bank of England, sent a letter to the Environmental Audit Committee (EAC). In the letter he stated that the FPC’s current assessment of the risks to financial stability were set out in the latest Financial Stability Report which was published on the 26<sup>th</sup> June 2014. That assessment showed that the FPC did not consider investment in high-carbon assets to be a material risk to financial stability at that time. However, Governor Carney did reassure the EAC that the FPC will continue to monitor a range of threats in its regular risk assessment, and will seek to discuss with the Committee on Climate Change if its assessment of risk associated with a carbon bubble changes.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-09-02T16:37:12.8388977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79304/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79304/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79304/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-22","Fossil Fuels","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will request the Financial Policy Committee (FPC) of the Bank of England to provide them with their most recent assessment of risks to UK financial stability arising from investment in high-carbon assets; and if he will place in the Library that request and the FPC response.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","207056"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79305","HM Treasury","false","2014-09-08","<p>HM Treasury has not produced any leaflets promoting the Government’s policy on the Scottish independence referendum.</p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2014-09-08T15:35:28.4645822Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79305/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79305/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79305/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-22","Sovereignty: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many leaflets produced by his Department promoting the Government's policy on the Scottish independence referendum have had to be amended, altered or destroyed; and at what cost to the public purse.","false","Biography information for Stewart Hosie","Dundee East","Stewart Hosie","207049"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79306","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-10-09","<p>This Government is committed to supporting people’s aspirations to own their own home.</p><p> </p><p>The Department does not collate statistics on the total number of first-time buyers at local authority level.</p><p> </p><p>The Help to Buy: Equity Loan scheme has been running for 17 months. The Department’s official statistics on sales for the Help to Buy: Equity Loan scheme, to 31 August 2014, broken down by local authority for England, are available at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/help-to-buy-equity-loan-scheme-monthly-statistics" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/help-to-buy-equity-loan-scheme-monthly-statistics</a>. In Worcester, the number of families buying a home with the support of the Help to Buy: Equity Loan scheme, as of 31 August 2014, was 79, of which 59 (75 per cent) were bought by first-time buyers.</p><p>The Government does not collect statistics for first-time buyers under Help to Buy: NewBuy. The latest official statistics, to 30 June 2014, are available at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/338725/20140731_Help_to_Buy_Equity_Loan_and_Help_to_Buy_NewBuy_statistical_release.pdf" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/338725/20140731_Help_to_Buy_Equity_Loan_and_Help_to_Buy_NewBuy_statistical_release.pdf</a>. There have been 7 sales in Worcester local authority until that point.</p><p>The Help to Buy: Mortgage Guarantee scheme is managed by HM Treasury and has been running for 12 months. Figures are currently available only for sales during the first nine months of the scheme, to 30 June 2014. There have been 39 sales in Worcester local authority until that point. The latest data is available at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/help-to-buy-mortgage-guarantee-scheme-quarterly-statistics-october-2013-to-june-2014" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/statistics/help-to-buy-mortgage-guarantee-scheme-quarterly-statistics-october-2013-to-june-2014</a>. This includes total numbers of sales at individual local authority level (Table 7) and UK-wide figures for the number of first-time buyers (Table 6).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-10-09T14:49:13.3272258Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79306/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79306/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79306/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-22","First Time Buyers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many first-time buyers have (a) bought properties in Worcester and (b) been helped by the help-to-buy scheme to purchase properties in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","206968"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79307","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-09-01","<p> </p><p>The Government is committed to improving information sharing, for the benefit of vulnerable children and adults, and all members of society. The statutory guidance, <em>Working Together to Safeguarding Children</em> requires all organisations to have arrangements in place which enable the effective sharing of information. Government Departments have been working to review procedures to identify children and adults at risk of abuse and the outcome of this review was published on 29 July and can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/working-together-to-safeguard-children-multi-agency-safeguarding-hubs" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/working-together-to-safeguard-children-multi-agency-safeguarding-hubs</a>. The Government is reviewing the guidance for practitioners and managers to dispel mistaken beliefs which prevent information being shared appropriately and effectively.</p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins","206970 ; 206971","2014-09-01T14:27:27.1932726Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79307/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79307/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79307/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-22","Children: Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what discussions (a) Ministers and (b) officials in his Department have had with counterparts in the Department for Education on his Department's Information Sharing Guidelines and child protection.","false","Biography information for Andy Sawford","Corby","Andy Sawford","206972"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79308","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-09-01","<p> </p><p>The Government is committed to improving information sharing, for the benefit of vulnerable children and adults, and all members of society. The statutory guidance, <em>Working Together to Safeguarding Children</em> requires all organisations to have arrangements in place which enable the effective sharing of information. Government Departments have been working to review procedures to identify children and adults at risk of abuse and the outcome of this review was published on 29 July and can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/working-together-to-safeguard-children-multi-agency-safeguarding-hubs" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/working-together-to-safeguard-children-multi-agency-safeguarding-hubs</a>. The Government is reviewing the guidance for practitioners and managers to dispel mistaken beliefs which prevent information being shared appropriately and effectively.</p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins","206971 ; 206972","2014-09-01T14:27:27.1151829Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79308/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79308/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79308/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-22","Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when he will update his Department's Information Sharing Guidance.","false","Biography information for Andy Sawford","Corby","Andy Sawford","206970"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79309","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-09-01","<p> </p><p>The Government is committed to improving information sharing, for the benefit of vulnerable children and adults, and all members of society. The statutory guidance, <em>Working Together to Safeguarding Children</em> requires all organisations to have arrangements in place which enable the effective sharing of information. Government Departments have been working to review procedures to identify children and adults at risk of abuse and the outcome of this review was published on 29 July and can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/working-together-to-safeguard-children-multi-agency-safeguarding-hubs" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/working-together-to-safeguard-children-multi-agency-safeguarding-hubs</a>. The Government is reviewing the guidance for practitioners and managers to dispel mistaken beliefs which prevent information being shared appropriately and effectively.</p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins","206970 ; 206972","2014-09-01T14:27:27.052649Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79309/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79309/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79309/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-22","Children: Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of his Department's Information Sharing Guidelines on providing professionals with information about sharing data in the interests of child protection; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andy Sawford","Corby","Andy Sawford","206971"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79310","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-09-24","<p> </p><p>The Government has taken no such steps to make any change to UK public documents.</p><p>The underlying issue stems from a proposed EU regulation (2013/0119) on the use of public documents between EU Member States. The draft can be found at: <a href="http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=COM:2013:0228:FIN:EN:PDF" target="_blank">http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=COM:2013:0228:FIN:EN:PDF</a></p><p>The UK Government has been absolutely clear that there can be no suggestion of national birth, death or marriage certificates being replaced by EU documents, or of UK emblems being replaced by EU branding on them. Further, the European Commission has stated that there is no EU legal basis to impose any such replacement.</p><p>Negotiations continue on this draft regulation<em>.</em> Ministers have been clear that the imposition of the EU flag is inappropriate<em>.</em> Indeed, following negotiations initiated by my rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government (Eric Pickles), the UK Government last year stopped proposals from the European Commission to make it compulsory for many public bodies to fly the EU flag from their public buildings all year round, and in addition, successfully renegotiated EU law to remove the previous requirement (under 2006 EU regulation) to fly the EU flag for one week a year on Europe Day.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2014-09-24T15:33:38.7530968Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79310/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79310/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79310/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-22","Registration of Births, Deaths, Marriages and Civil Partnerships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps the Government has taken to implement the EU proposal to replace the royal coat of arms with the EU emblem on birth, death and marriage certificates; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","206993"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79312","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-09-01","PMSE users currently have dedicated access to spectrum in channel 38 (between 606MHz and 614MHz) as well as access to interleaved spectrum for which no new equipment is required. Ofcom published a consultation on 24 April 2013 on the future use of the 700MHz band, and will ensure the views and spectrum requirements of the PMSE community and any other wireless microphone users are taken into account when advising on any decision. The consultation document and responses can be found on Ofcom’s website: http://stakeholders.ofcom.org.uk/consultations/700mhz-cfi/ There are also currently discussions in Europe on future spectrum provision for PMSE users and the potential requirement for further dedicated spectrum for these purposes.","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","206933 ; 206945 ; 206946","2014-09-01T10:51:55.8364906Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79312/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79312/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79312/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-22","Radio Frequencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on (a) places of worship and (b) community centres of loss of access by wireless microphone users to the 700 MHz band of radio spectrum; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mike Weatherley","Hove","Mike Weatherley","206934"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79313","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-09-01","PMSE users currently have dedicated access to spectrum in channel 38 (between 606MHz and 614MHz) as well as access to interleaved spectrum for which no new equipment is required. Ofcom published a consultation on 24 April 2013 on the future use of the 700MHz band, and will ensure the views and spectrum requirements of the PMSE community and any other wireless microphone users are taken into account when advising on any decision. The consultation document and responses can be found on Ofcom’s website: http://stakeholders.ofcom.org.uk/consultations/700mhz-cfi/ There are also currently discussions in Europe on future spectrum provision for PMSE users and the potential requirement for further dedicated spectrum for these purposes.","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","206933 ; 206934 ; 206946","2014-09-01T10:51:55.9615268Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79313/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79313/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79313/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-22","Radio Frequencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on the (a) film industry and (b) television production industry of a loss of access by wireless microphone users to the 700 MHz band of radio spectrum; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mike Weatherley","Hove","Mike Weatherley","206945"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79314","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-09-01","The Government warmly welcomed the initiative by copyright owners and ISPs of setting up Creative Content UK, and has pledged £3.5 million over three years to support the educational campaign that will complement the process. An industry-led solution has always been our preferred approach, and so Government will not progress the relevant provisions within the Digital Economy Act 2010 at this time. However, they will remain available if a legislative solution becomes necessary.","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-09-01T10:56:09.8037224Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79314/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79314/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79314/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-22","Copyright: Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what his policy is on the development by ISPs and copyright owners of Creative Content UK, a programme of education about legal entertainment services, and alerts to subscribers found to have been uploading content illegally online; and what effects he expects the development to have on the implementation of the Digital Economy Act 2010.","false","Biography information for Mike Weatherley","Hove","Mike Weatherley","206927"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79315","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-09-01","The BFI Triennial Review Report is being prepared for publication and will be published shortly. The House will be informed of the publication through a Written Ministerial Statement.","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-09-01T11:09:45.6209472Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79315/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79315/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79315/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-22","British Film Institute","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, when he expects that the Triennial Review of the British Film Institute will be published.","false","Biography information for Sir Roger Gale","North Thanet","Sir Roger Gale","206926"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79316","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-09-01","<p>Ofcom published a consultation on the future use of the 700 MHz band on 28 May 2014. This consultation assesses the impact any loss of access to the 700 MHz band would have on the PMSE community. Ofcom will ensure the views and spectrum requirements of the PMSE community are taken into account when making any final decisions on the use of the band. The consultation document and responses can be found on Ofcom’s website:</p><p><a href="http://stakeholders.ofcom.org.uk/consultations/700MHz/" target="_blank">http://stakeholders.ofcom.org.uk/consultations/700MHz/</a></p><p>Ofcom is working with the PMSE community of users and manufacturers to mitigate the impact of any change of use of the 700 MHz band; and discussing with the regulatory authorities in other countries their approach to this issue. A key focus of their work in this area is seeking to identify and make available alternative spectrum for the PMSE community.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","206818 ; 206821 ; 206823 ; 206936 ; 206943 ; 206944","2014-09-01T10:45:25.1899719Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79316/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79316/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79316/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-22","Broadcasting: Radio Frequencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on the programme making and special events (PMSE) sector of a loss of access by PMSE users to the 700 MHz band of radio spectrum; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mike Weatherley","Hove","Mike Weatherley","206947"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79317","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-09-01","PMSE users currently have dedicated access to spectrum in channel 38 (between 606MHz and 614MHz) as well as access to interleaved spectrum for which no new equipment is required. Ofcom published a consultation on 24 April 2013 on the future use of the 700MHz band, and will ensure the views and spectrum requirements of the PMSE community and any other wireless microphone users are taken into account when advising on any decision. The consultation document and responses can be found on Ofcom’s website: http://stakeholders.ofcom.org.uk/consultations/700mhz-cfi/ There are also currently discussions in Europe on future spectrum provision for PMSE users and the potential requirement for further dedicated spectrum for these purposes.","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","206933 ; 206934 ; 206945","2014-09-01T10:51:56.0240288Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79317/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79317/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79317/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-22","Broadcasting: Radio Frequencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on the UK's ability to host future major sporting or cultural events of a loss of access by programme making and special events users to the 700 MHz band of radio spectrum; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mike Weatherley","Hove","Mike Weatherley","206946"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79318","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-09-02","<p>Lottery distributors do not allocate their funding on a constituency basis. While they are required to ensure that Lottery funding is available to all areas and all sections of society, they make their funding decisions based on an assessment of applications submitted to each of their separate funding streams. A database of all Lottery grants is compiled by DCMS from data supplied by the various Lottery distributors. The database is available at: <a href="http://www.lottery.culture.gov.uk/Search.aspx" target="_blank">http://www.lottery.culture.gov.uk/Search.aspx</a> and is searchable in a variety of ways, including by constituency.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-09-02T09:24:59.0233288Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79318/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79318/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79318/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-22","National Lottery: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how much the National Lottery Distribution Fund has allocated to each parliamentary constituency in Scotland in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Frank Roy","Motherwell and Wishaw","Mr Frank Roy","206973"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79319","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-09-01","The Responsible Gambling Trust (RGT) has commissioned a wide-ranging research programme into category B2 gaming machines which is due to be published in the Autumn. This research will seek to understand what measures might limit harmful play without impacting on those who do not exhibit harmful behaviours and the RGT has commissioned the University of Lincoln to determine whether gambling at higher stakes is a risk factor for gambling-related harm and to explore the impact of higher stakes and prizes on players.","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-09-01T11:19:28.4868802Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79319/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79319/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79319/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-22","Gaming Machines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether the research being conducted by Lincoln University on fixed odds betting terminals will assess the potentially addictive nature of those machines.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","207030"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79320","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-09-01","The Responsible Gambling Trust (RGT) has commissioned a wide-ranging research programme into category B2 gaming machines which is due to be published in the Autumn. This research will seek to understand what measures might limit harmful play without impacting on those who do not exhibit harmful behaviours and the RGT has commissioned the University of Lincoln to determine whether gambling at higher stakes is a risk factor for gambling-related harm and to explore the impact of higher stakes and prizes on players.","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-09-01T11:20:45.4969493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79320/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79320/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79320/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-22","Gaming Machines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether the research being conducted by Lincoln University on fixed odds betting terminals will help determine an appropriate stake level for those machines.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","207031"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79321","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-05","<p>The Service Personnel and Veterans Agency, now Veterans UK, received the following number of complaints about the standard of customer service received, categorised into the Armed Forces Pension Scheme (AFPS), War Pensions Scheme (WPS) and Armed Forces Compensation Scheme (AFCS). The number of complaints about standards of customer service from military personnel were only counted from January 2014. <br><br>2010<br>AFPS 30<br>WPS/AFCS 445<br>Total Complaints 475<br><br>2011<br>AFPS 15<br>WPS/AFCS 420<br>Total Complaints 435<br><br>2012<br>AFPS 10<br>WPS/AFCS 460<br>Total Complaints 470<br><br>2013<br>AFPS 30<br>WPS/AFCS 290<br>Total Complaints 320<br><br>2014 (to 31 July)<br>AFPS 25<br>WPS/AFCS 95<br>Military Personnel 10<br>Total Complaints 130</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-09-05T12:18:06.0082069Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79321/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79321/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79321/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-22","Service Personnel and Veterans Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many complaints the Service Personnel and Veterans Agency received in each year since 2010; and whether those complaints have been categorised.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","207037"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79322","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-02","<p>The guideline period in which an application for an armed forces pension should be processed and delivered is: <br><br>Awards are to be calculated, authorised and payment instructions established for entitled individuals within 10 working days of the termination date or receipt of all documentation, whichever is the later. Only one application exceeded that guideline period for the year 2013-14, with none this year to end July 2014</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-09-02T14:27:00.060273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79322/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79322/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79322/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-22","Armed Forces: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the guideline period is in which an application for an armed forces pension should be (a) processed and (b) delivered; and how many applications have exceeded that guideline period to date.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","207035"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79323","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-04","<p> </p><p>Veterans UK and the former Service Personnel and Veterans Agency are part of Defence Business Services (DBS) and form part of the Ministry of Defence (MOD). DBS is responsible and accountable to the MOD Permanent Under Secretary and Ministers who are answerable to Parliament.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","207033","2014-09-04T11:58:51.8885229Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79323/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79323/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79323/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-22","Service Personnel and Veterans Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what checks and balances he put in place to ensure that the Service Personnel and Veterans Agency was accountable to his Department.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","207038"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79324","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-01","<p>The Armed Forces Pension Scheme is an occupational pension scheme whereby the recipient has entitlement based on their reckonable service in HM Forces. Every effort is made to make the Armed Forces Pension Scheme application form (Pen1) as simple as possible whilst ensuring that all salient points are included, particularly for legal reasons.</p><p> </p><p>There is an online version of the application form which pre-fills several boxes using data taken directly from the Service person’s record. Current statistics on its use against paper applications are below which demonstrates its success.</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="2"> </td><td colspan="3"><p><strong>January - June 2014</strong></p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td><td><p><strong>Electronic</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Hard Copy</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>January</strong></p></td><td><p>1352</p></td><td><p>242</p></td><td><p>1594</p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>February</strong></p></td><td><p>1174</p></td><td><p>193</p></td><td><p>1367</p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>March</strong></p></td><td><p>1131</p></td><td><p>256</p></td><td><p>1387</p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>April</strong></p></td><td><p>1081</p></td><td><p>148</p></td><td><p>1229</p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>May</strong></p></td><td><p>1166</p></td><td><p>167</p></td><td><p>1333</p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>June</strong></p></td><td><p>1493</p></td><td><p>200</p></td><td><p>1693</p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>7397</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>1206</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>8603</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>Average %</strong></p></td><td><p>86%</p></td><td><p>14%</p></td><td><p>100%</p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-09-01T13:06:28.1081828Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79324/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79324/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79324/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-22","Armed Forces: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when designing the application process for the armed forces pension, what weight his Department gave to the ease of use of the system.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","207036"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79325","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-04","<p>The RAF Waddington International Air Show is the RAF’s largest official Air Show and aims to raise awareness of the RAF and its activities and to raise money for charity. It has attracted an average attendance of 130,000 for the two day event over the past five years. Since 1995, £3.3 million has been raised and donated to charities.<br><br>The 2015 Air Show has been cancelled due to essential work due to be carried out on the RAF Waddington runway. <br><br>The RAF is reviewing Air Show commitments from 2016 onwards. The results of this review will be announced in due course.</p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-09-04T11:57:37.8271977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79325/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79325/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79325/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-22","RAF Waddington","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent assessment his Department has made of the effect of the RAF Air Show at RAF Waddington on (a) the public profile of the RAF, (b) public interest in the RAF and (c) money raised for RAF charities; and what plans he has for the future of the air show at RAF Waddington.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Lewis","New Forest East","Dr Julian Lewis","207015"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79326","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-04","<p> </p><p>Veterans UK and the former Service Personnel and Veterans Agency are part of Defence Business Services (DBS) and form part of the Ministry of Defence (MOD). DBS is responsible and accountable to the MOD Permanent Under Secretary and Ministers who are answerable to Parliament.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","207038","2014-09-04T11:58:51.0970955Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79326/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79326/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79326/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-22","Veterans UK","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what checks and balances he has put in place to ensure that Veterans UK is accountable to his Department.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","207033"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79327","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-01","<p> </p><p>Veterans UK was formed on 1 April 2014 as part of the merger of the Service Personnel and Veterans Agency into Defence Business Services.<br><br>Veterans UK has received a total of 122 complaints since April 2014. These are broken down into 25 Armed Forces Pension Scheme, and 97 War Pension and Armed Forces Compensation Scheme complaints.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-09-01T13:04:25.7152286Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79327/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79327/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79327/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-22","Veterans UK","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many complaints Veterans UK has received since its creation; and whether those complaints have been categorised.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","207034"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79328","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-01","<p> </p><p>The Nato Eurofighter Tornado Management Agency has awarded a contract valued at approximately £120 million to Eurofighter GmbH for the integration of Storm Shadow onto Typhoon. <br><br>The full UK costs of the integration project are still being finalised but will be published in the National Audit Office Major Projects Report later in 2014.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-09-01T12:54:23.2582736Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79328/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79328/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79328/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-22","Guided Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will estimate the cost to the public purse of the integration of the Storm Shadow missile on the Typhoon aircraft.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","206989"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79329","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-01","<p>Enhancements to the Sentinel R1 aircraft are currently the subject of commercial negotiations. I am therefore withholding details of the potential costs, as the disclosure of this information would be prejudicial to the commercial interests of the Ministry of Defence.</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-09-01T12:55:11.1186664Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79329/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79329/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79329/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-22","Military Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the cost to the public purse of expanding the capabilities of the Sentinel R.1.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","206985"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79330","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-06","<p>No decisions have been taken on the integration of Brimstone 2 on UK Apache Helicopters or UK armed Remotely Piloted Air Systems.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-10-06T15:33:49.2824538Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79330/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79330/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79330/answer","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79330/answer/previousversion/18492","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-22","Guided Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what consideration his Department has given to integrating the Brimstone 2 missile onto Apache AH.1 attack helicopters MQ-9 Reaper unmanned aerial vehicles.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","206984"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79331","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-01","<p>The Heavy and Light Future Anti-Surface Guided Weapon systems will be introduced to Wildcat maritime helicopters with a planned in-service date of 2020.</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-09-01T12:49:53.8981771Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79331/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79331/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79331/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-22","Guided Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what his policy is on the introduction of the (a) Heavy and (b) Light Future Anti-Surface Guided Weapon Systems on AW159 Wildcat Helicopters; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","206994"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79332","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-01","<p> </p><p>A requirement for a new common jamming pod was first identified in 2012. The total approved value of the project is £50.9 million.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-09-01T12:53:27.8661889Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79332/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79332/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79332/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-22","Tornado Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the cost of the new common jamming pod for the Tornado aircraft; and when the requirement for that pod was first identified.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","206987"
