"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79455","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-01","<p>The independent review of the ‘fee for intervention’ scheme operated by the Health and Safety Executive (HSE) has completed and I am considering its recommendations. The report will be published later this year.</p><p> </p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-09-01T13:39:48.7386313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79455/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79455/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79455/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-22","Health and Safety Executive","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when he estimates he will (a) receive and (b) publish the findings of the Health and Safety Executive Review Panel on Fee for Intervention.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","207024"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79456","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-01","<p>In order to drive good performance and thereby support as many people into sustained work as possible, the Department reviewed the market shares of Work Programme providers, based on performance delivered during the 12 months ending 31 March 2013, and adjusted shares accordingly from August 2013.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is reviewing the performance of its Work Programme prime providers in the 12 months to the end of March 2014 and will advise the House where prevailing market shares are to change.</p><p> </p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-09-01T15:10:43.0815955Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79456/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79456/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79456/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-22","Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the market shift mechanism in the Work Programme.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","207025"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79457","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-01","<p>The Health and Work Service procurement (which followed an Open procurement route) has now concluded. We received four expressions of interest. These were from Health Management Ltd, Ingeus UK Ltd, OPTUM and SOMA.</p><p> </p><p>The successful organisation was Health Management Ltd.</p><p> </p><p>The winning tender and contract was published on Contracts Finder on 21 August 2014.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-09-01T13:56:41.7717489Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79457/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79457/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79457/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-22","Occupational Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what companies have expressed an interest to his Department in tendering for the Health and Work Service.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","207023"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79458","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-01","<p>There is an available budget for the Health and Work Service across Great Britain of £38.4m in 2014/15 to cover set-up and live running, and £38.4m in 2015/16 to cover live running.</p><p> </p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-09-01T14:15:08.5970104Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79458/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79458/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79458/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-22","Occupational Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the budget of the Health and Work Service will be in (a) 2014-15 and (b) 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","207021"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79459","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-01","<p>Cases are dealt with individually therefore there is not set length. All claims are processed as quickly &amp; efficiently as possible. There is no statutory time limit. We deliberately do not have one because each case will be considered on its merits. Some will require just days, others longer.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey","207019","2014-09-01T14:56:20.9451547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79459/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79459/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79459/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-07-22","Jobseeker's Allowance: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how long it takes for (a) successful and (b) unsuccessful challenges to jobseeker's allowance sanctions to be processed.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","207020"
