"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79191","Home Office","false","2014-08-11","<p>Citizens of the following countries and territories require visas to visit the UK but not the Republic of Ireland: Bolivia, Fiji, Guyana, Lesotho, Malawi, South Africa, Swaziland and Taiwan.</p>",,"Lord Taylor of Holbeach",,"2014-08-11T12:44:34.8356678Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79191/answer","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Holbeach","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79191/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79191/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-21","Entry Clearances","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether there are any citizens of foreign countries who require a visa to enter the United Kingdom but who do not require a visa to enter the Republic of Ireland.","false","Biography information for Lord Ashcroft",,"Lord Ashcroft","HL1352"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79192","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-08-11","<p>The Government has made no assessment of the number of British and British-Israeli citizens serving in the Israeli Defence Force (IDF). Any UK national serving abroad in the armed forces of any state is bound by the laws of armed conflict and any local laws that apply.</p>",,"Baroness Warsi","HL1354","2014-08-11T10:34:49.4703623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79192/answer","Biography information for Baroness Warsi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79192/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79192/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-21","Israel","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their estimate of the total number of dual national British–Israeli citizens serving in the Israeli Defence Force.","false","Biography information for Lord Ahmed",,"Lord Ahmed","HL1353"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79193","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-08-11","<p>The Government has made no assessment of the number of British and British-Israeli citizens serving in the Israeli Defence Force (IDF). Any UK national serving abroad in the armed forces of any state is bound by the laws of armed conflict and any local laws that apply.</p>",,"Baroness Warsi","HL1353","2014-08-11T10:34:50.2113487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79193/answer","Biography information for Baroness Warsi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79193/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79193/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-21","Israel","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their estimate of the number of British citizens engaged in operations against the Palestinian people in Gaza.","false","Biography information for Lord Ahmed",,"Lord Ahmed","HL1354"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79194","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-08-11","The Government has made no assessment of the number of British and British-Israeli citizens serving in the Israeli Defence Force (IDF). Any UK national serving abroad in the armed forces of any state is bound by the laws of armed conflict and any local laws that apply.",,"Baroness Warsi",,"2014-08-11T11:49:40.056819Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79194/answer","Biography information for Baroness Warsi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79194/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79194/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-21","Israel","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they intend to take any action against those British citizens serving in the Israeli Defence Force.","false","Biography information for Lord Ahmed",,"Lord Ahmed","HL1355"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79195","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-08-11","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) publishes travel advice on its website for any British citizens planning to travel to Israel and the Occupied Palestinian Territories. The FCO currently advises against all travel to Gaza.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Warsi",,"2014-08-11T11:46:45.4894833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79195/answer","Biography information for Baroness Warsi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79195/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79195/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-21","Israel","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they have published any information for the British citizens travelling to Israel regarding the possibility of their involvement in operations in Gaza.","false","Biography information for Lord Ahmed",,"Lord Ahmed","HL1356"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79196","Department for International Development","false","2014-08-11","<p> </p><p>We have released £10million since the latest crisis began. We are giving the UN Relief and Works Agency £4 million in new funding to provide health care, clean water, blankets and cooking equipment to help tens of thousands of Palestinians affected by the violence in Gaza, and £3million to the UN World Food Programme to provide food vouchers to vulnerable families. We are also bringing forward £3 million to support the work of the International Committee of the Red Cross in repairing water infrastructure and providing emergency medical support.</p><p> </p><p>DFID is already spending almost £350million from 2011-2015 to address a broad range of Palestinian development and humanitarian needs, of which approximately £30million per annum is spent on Gaza.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Wallace of Saltaire",,"2014-08-11T12:04:29.1661716Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79196/answer","Biography information for Lord Wallace of Saltaire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79196/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79196/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-21","Palestinians","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they have sent emergency aid for the children of Gaza including medical, food and shelter.","false","Biography information for Lord Ahmed",,"Lord Ahmed","HL1357"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79197","Department of Health","false","2014-07-29","<p>Use of a sample type not indicated by the manufacturer would be considered to be off label use of the device. This off label use is not regulated by the Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency and would be the responsibility of the laboratory.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2014-07-29T13:16:10.1285003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79197/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79197/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79197/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-21","Lyme Disease","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Earl Howe on 25 June 2012 (WA 21–2), whether they consider that the use of the CE-marked Trinity Biotech EU Lyme western blot test, when used with cerebrospinal fluid, would constitute "use of an in-house test" as defined by the Medical and Healthcare Products Regulatory Agency guidance.","false","Biography information for The Countess of Mar",,"The Countess of Mar","HL1358"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79198","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-07-28","<p>I have noted the recommendations of the British Academy and the Honor Frost Foundation. DCMS will begin reviewing the conclusions of the recent Impact Report on the UNESCO Convention on the Protection of the Underwater Cultural Heritage later this year.</p>",,"Baroness Jolly",,"2014-07-28T11:51:27.6963711Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79198/answer","Biography information for Baroness Jolly","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79198/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79198/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-21","Convention on the Protection of the Underwater Cultural Heritage","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the recommendation by the British Academy and the Honor Frost Foundation to the Foreign Secretary on 20 March that the United Kingdom should ratify the 2001 UNESCO Convention on the Protection of the Underwater Cultural Heritage.","false","Biography information for Lord Renfrew of Kaimsthorn",,"Lord Renfrew of Kaimsthorn","HL1359"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79199","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-08-11","<p>The legislative priorities for this session were set out in the Queen’s speech in June. The Government remains committed to protecting cultural heritage and we will seek to legislate on the 1954 Hague Convention and the subsequent protocols when parliamentary time allows. The 1954 convention already informs the Armed Forces’ law of armed conflict doctrine and training policy, particularly with regard to respect for cultural property, precautions in attack and recognition of the protective emblem.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is deeply concerned by reports of damage to cultural property in Syria and Northern Iraq, including recent attacks by Islamic State of Iraq and Levant against Mosques, Churches and other holy places. The reported destruction of the Tomb of Yonus (Jonah) in Mosul on 24 July by ISIL is further evidence of the groups barbarism and disregard for International Humanitarian Law. We are also concerned that Syria’s cultural heritage is being plundered for private profit. That is why in December 2013 the UK and other EU nations amended the EU’s sanctions regime to make clear that involvement in trade relating to artefacts illegally removed from Syria is prohibited. This will help safeguard Syria’s cultural heritage for the future and we will continue to do all we can to bring an end to the conflict and restore stability in the region.</p>",,"Lord Wallace of Saltaire",,"2014-08-11T12:48:09.6217849Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79199/answer","Biography information for Lord Wallace of Saltaire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79199/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/79199/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-21","UN Convention for Protection of Cultural Property in Event of Armed Conflict","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the answer by Lord Gardiner of Kimble on 12 May (HL Deb, col 1650), when they expect there to be parliamentary time to introduce legislation to ratify the 1954 Convention for the Protection of Cultural Property in the Event of Armed Conflict; and what assessment they have made of the damage to cultural property in the recent and continuing armed conflict in Syria and northern Iraq.","false","Biography information for Lord Renfrew of Kaimsthorn",,"Lord Renfrew of Kaimsthorn","HL1360"
